        "**Parallelism Strategies**: Tensor parallelism shards individual layers across multiple devices, reducing per-device memory requirements, while pipeline parallelism distributes consecutive layers to different devices, increasing throughput by overlapping computation and communication. This figure contrasts these approaches, highlighting how tensor parallelism replicates layer parameters across devices and pipeline parallelism partitions the model’s computational graph.\n",
